The paper deals with the optimization of channel state information (CSI) feedback in a multicell MIMO system, which falls under the information theory (cs.IT) and networking and internet architecture (cs.NI) categories. The paper also discusses the use of pathloss structure to reduce the amount of feedback necessary, which is related to signal processing (cs.SI) and multimedia (cs.MM). Additionally, the paper proposes a new approach to allocate CSI feedback, which involves optimization and game theory, falling under the categories of theoretical computer science (cs.GT).
